```sql
WITH deduped_billing_events AS (
  SELECT 
    subscription_id,
    event_month,
    amount,
    event_type,
    ROW_NUMBER() OVER (
      PARTITION BY subscription_id, event_month 
      ORDER BY event_id
    ) AS rn
  FROM billing_events
)
SELECT 
  subscription_id,
  event_month,
  amount,
  event_type
FROM deduped_billing_events
WHERE rn = 1;
```

-- monthly_metrics.sql
```sql
WITH deduped_billing_events AS (
  SELECT 
    subscription_id,
    event_month,
    amount,
    ROW_NUMBER() OVER (
      PARTITION BY subscription_id, event_month 
      ORDER BY event_id
    ) AS rn
  FROM billing_events
),
billing_deduped AS (
  SELECT 
    subscription_id,
    event_month,
    amount
  FROM deduped_billing_events
  WHERE rn = 1
),
subscription_details AS (
  SELECT 
    s.subscription_id,
    s.user_id,
    s.started_at,
    s.ended_at,
    s.status,
    COALESCE(p.tier, 'Unknown') AS tier
  FROM subscriptions s
  LEFT JOIN plans p ON s.plan_id = p.plan_id
),
user_details AS (
  SELECT 
    u.user_id,
    COALESCE(c.industry, 'Unknown') AS industry
  FROM users u
  LEFT JOIN companies c ON u.company_id = c.company_id
)
SELECT 
  DATE_TRUNC('month', be.event_month)::DATE AS month,
  sd.tier,
  ud.industry,
  COUNT(DISTINCT sd.subscription_id) AS active_subscriptions,
  SUM(be.amount) AS total_mrr,
  COUNT(DISTINCT sd.user_id) AS unique_users
FROM billing_deduped be
JOIN subscription_details sd ON be.subscription_id = sd.subscription_id
JOIN user_details ud ON sd.user_id = ud.user_id
WHERE sd.status = 'active'
GROUP BY 
  DATE_TRUNC('month', be.event_month)::DATE,
  sd.tier,
  ud.industry
ORDER BY month, sd.tier, ud.industry;
